cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use KakeyaLattice in academic work or in a production deployment, please cite it using the entry below. Preferred citation is the software release; the companion technical report provides the full derivation."
title: "KakeyaLattice: Nested-Lattice KV-Cache Compression for Large Language Models"
abstract: "KakeyaLattice is a drop-in subclass of transformers.DynamicCache that compresses the KV cache of modern transformer language models 2.4x-2.8x at under 1 percent perplexity loss using nested D4 / E8 lattice quantisation of Sylvester-Hadamard-rotated, adaptively L2-scaled key/value vectors. Verified on Qwen3, Llama-3, DeepSeek-R1-Distill, GLM-4-9B-Chat, and Gemma-4-E4B with real vLLM prefill and real FlashAttention bfloat16 forward on NVIDIA H200 at 128k context."
type: software
authors:
